8 Section 2. Section 33-22-128, MCA, is amended to read:
9 "33-22-128. Coverage for children with hearing loss -- definitions. (1) Health insurance coverage
10 sold in the group or individual market in this state must provide coverage for diagnosis and treatment of hearing
11 loss for a covered child 18 years of age or younger person in accordance with subsection (2).
12 (2) (a) Except as provided in subsection (2)(b), coverage under this section, in addition to
13 diagnosis, must include treatment that is:
14 (i) a medical necessity; and
15 (ii) prescribed, provided, or ordered by a licensed health care provider to treat hearing loss of the
16 covered child person.
17 (b) Treatment may not include more than one hearing device with required accessories or
18 amplification device with required accessories for each ear every 3 years or as required by an audiologist
19 licensed under Title 37, chapter 15.
20 (3) Benefits provided under this section may not be construed as limiting physical health benefits
21 that are otherwise available to the covered child person.
22 (4) (a) Coverage under this section may be subject to deductibles, coinsurance, and copayment
23 provisions and utilization review as provided in Title 33, chapter 32.
24 (b) Special deductible, coinsurance, copayment, or other limitations that are not generally
25 applicable to other medical care covered under the plan may not be imposed on the coverage under this
26 section.
27 (5) This section also applies to the state employee group insurance program, the university system
28 employee group insurance program, any employee group insurance program of a city, town, school district, or
